items.title: The Google Search of AI agents? Fetch launches ASI:One and Business tier for new era of non-human web
items.summary: Fetch AI announced the release of three interconnected products designed to provide the trust, coordination, and interoperability needed for large-scale AI agent ecosystems . The launch includes a personal-AI orchestration platform, a verification and discovery portal for brand agents; and an open directory hosting more than two million agents . The company says the tools address a central limitation in current consumer AI: models can provide recommendations but cannot reliably execute multi-step actions .

items.title: OpenCV founders launch AI video startup to take on OpenAI and Google
items.summary: New AI startup CraftStory has emerged from stealth with technology that generates realistic human-centric videos up to five minutes long . CraftStory's system can produce continuous, coherent video performances that run as long as a typical YouTube tutorial or product demonstration . The breakthrough could unlock substantial commercial value for enterprises struggling to scale video production for training, marketing, and customer education .

items.title: VentureBeat launches “Beyond the Pilot” — a new podcast series exploring how enterprise AI gets real
items.summary: VentureBeat announces the launch of its new flagship podcast, Beyond the Pilot: Enterprise AI in Action . The podcast is designed for senior managers, directors, VPs, and lead engineers responsible for turning AI strategy into tangible results . The debut episode features Notion, where VP AI Ryan Nystrom discusses how the company built Notion 3.0 for agents .

items.title: Meta’s DreamGym framework trains AI agents in a simulated world to cut reinforcement learning costs
items.summary: Researchers at Meta, the University of Chicago, and UC Berkeley have developed a new framework that addresses the high costs, infrastructure complexity, and unreliable feedback associated with using reinforcement learning (RL) to train large language model (LLM) agents . The framework, DreamGym, simulates an RL environment to train agents for complex applications . As it progresses through the training process, the framework dynamically adjusts task difficulty .

items.title: Investing in America 2025
items.summary: Google’s deep investments in American technical infrastructure, R&D and the workforce will help the U.S. continue to lead the world in AI, Google says . Google's deep investments will help American tech companies continue to develop and compete in artificial intelligence, the company said in a new blog post on Monday . Google says it is investing in the American workforce and infrastructure to develop AI technology .
